org.openliberty.openaz.pep
Class PepResponseImpl

java.lang.Object
  org.openliberty.openaz.pep.PepResponseImpl
All Implemented Interfaces:
PepResponse
public class PepResponseImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements PepResponse

PepResponse is the main entry point for processing the results of a PepRequestImpl.decide() call.
It enables processing one result at a time for an AzResponseContext, which may contain multiple decisions from one of the

  • PepRequestFactoryImpl.newBulkPepRequest(Object, java.util.List, Object) calls,
or a
  • PepRequestFactory.newQueryPepRequest(Object, Object, String, PepRequestQueryType) call.
It also provides a wrapper around the AzResponseContext which enables access to the underlying low level AzApi funtions.

Please refer to PepRequestFactoryImpl for code example containing processing of a PepResponse.

next

public boolean next()
             throws PepException
For bulk requests and query requests, move the iterator to the next result. For bulk requests and query requests, the iterator initially points prior to the first result. For single newPepRequest, the iterator always points to the first and only result and next() always returns false.

Specified by:

Returns:
